{
  "files": [
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/annotation_key_constants.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/api/discovery/v1/types.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/api/events/v1/types.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/api/events/v1beta1/types.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "pkg/apis/core/annotation_key_constants.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "pkg/apis/discovery/types.go"}
  ],
  "text": "Kubernetes API types define multiple deprecated struct fields and constants that are maintained for backward compatibility. In the core API types, DeprecatedServiceAccount is a deprecated alias for ServiceAccountName in Pod specifications. The discovery API defines DeprecatedTopology in the Endpoint struct for v1 API and internal types, providing round-trip compatibility with the v1beta1 API. The events API defines several deprecated fields in Event structs for v1 and v1beta1: DeprecatedSource, DeprecatedFirstTimestamp, DeprecatedLastTimestamp, and DeprecatedCount, all assuring backward compatibility with core.v1 Event types. Annotation constants include DeprecatedSeccompProfileDockerDefault, which represents the deprecated docker default seccomp profile, as well as several deprecated AppArmor-related constants: DeprecatedAppArmorAnnotationKeyPrefix, DeprecatedAppArmorAnnotationValueRuntimeDefault, and DeprecatedAppArmorAnnotationValueLocalhostPrefix (in pkg/apis), plus DeprecatedAppArmorBetaContainerAnnotationKeyPrefix, DeprecatedAppArmorBetaProfileRuntimeDefault, DeprecatedAppArmorBetaProfileNamePrefix, and DeprecatedAppArmorBetaProfileNameUnconfined (in staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1). Additionally, DeprecatedAnnotationTopologyAwareHints is defined for topology-aware hints annotation keys. These deprecated fields remain in the API for backward compatibility but users are directed to use newer alternatives."
}

